 labels = {["strong"]}>
Set of dedicated &quot;absolute&quot; execution weights for a block.

<EnumerationList title="Enumeration values">

<EnumerationListItem name="UNREACHABLE">

Unreachable-terminating branch taken probability.

This is the probability for a branch being taken to a block that terminates (eventually) in unreachable. These are predicted as unlikely as possible. All reachable probability will proportionally share the remaining part.

<Link id="l00451" /><CodeLine lineNumber="451"><span class="doxyHighlight">    &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00452" /><CodeLine lineNumber="452"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00453" /><CodeLine lineNumber="453"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Sum of all edge probabilities must be 1.0. If we modified the probability</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00454" /><CodeLine lineNumber="454"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// of some edges then we must distribute the introduced difference over the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00455" /><CodeLine lineNumber="455"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// reachable blocks.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00456" /><CodeLine lineNumber="456"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00457" /><CodeLine lineNumber="457"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Proportional distribution: the relation between probabilities of the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00458" /><CodeLine lineNumber="458"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// reachable edges is kept unchanged. That is for any reachable edges i and j:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00459" /><CodeLine lineNumber="459"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   newBP&#91;i&#93; / newBP&#91;j&#93; == oldBP&#91;i&#93; / oldBP&#91;j&#93; =&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00460" /><CodeLine lineNumber="460"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   newBP&#91;i&#93; / oldBP&#91;i&#93; == newBP&#91;j&#93; / oldBP&#91;j&#93; == K</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00461" /><CodeLine lineNumber="461"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Where K is independent of i,j.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00462" /><CodeLine lineNumber="462"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   newBP&#91;i&#93; == oldBP&#91;i&#93; &#42; K</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00463" /><CodeLine lineNumber="463"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// We need to find K.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00464" /><CodeLine lineNumber="464"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Make sum of all reachables of the left and right parts:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00465" /><CodeLine lineNumber="465"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   sum&#95;of&#95;reachable(newBP) == K &#42; sum&#95;of&#95;reachable(oldBP)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00466" /><CodeLine lineNumber="466"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Sum of newBP must be equal to 1.0:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00467" /><CodeLine lineNumber="467"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   sum&#95;of&#95;reachable(newBP) + sum&#95;of&#95;unreachable(newBP) == 1 =&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00468" /><CodeLine lineNumber="468"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   sum&#95;of&#95;reachable(newBP) = 1 - sum&#95;of&#95;unreachable(newBP)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00469" /><CodeLine lineNumber="469"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Where sum&#95;of&#95;unreachable(newBP) is what has been just changed.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00470" /><CodeLine lineNumber="470"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Finally:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00471" /><CodeLine lineNumber="471"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   K == sum&#95;of&#95;reachable(newBP) / sum&#95;of&#95;reachable(oldBP) =&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00472" /><CodeLine lineNumber="472"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   K == (1.0 - sum&#95;of&#95;unreachable(newBP)) / sum&#95;of&#95;reachable(oldBP)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00473" /><CodeLine lineNumber="473"><span class="doxyHighlight">  BranchProbability NewUnreachableSum = <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/branchprobability/#afd00958cba7080048a84cccfcef55d71">BranchProbability::getZero</a>();</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00474" /><CodeLine lineNumber="474"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">for</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">auto</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/support/md5-cpp/#ac0eafdc9ee161b71e7af98af736952fd">I</a> : UnreachableIdxs)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00475" /><CodeLine lineNumber="475"><span class="doxyHighlight">    NewUnreachableSum += BP&#91;<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/support/md5-cpp/#ac0eafdc9ee161b71e7af98af736952fd">I</a>&#93;;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00476" /><CodeLine lineNumber="476"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00477" /><CodeLine lineNumber="477"><span class="doxyHighlight">  BranchProbability NewReachableSum =</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00478" /><CodeLine lineNumber="478"><span class="doxyHighlight">      <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/branchprobability/#a56e1b2d1999aadf4c513caee1ce5275b">BranchProbability::getOne</a>() - NewUnreachableSum;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00479" /><CodeLine lineNumber="479"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00480" /><CodeLine lineNumber="480"><span class="doxyHighlight">  BranchProbability OldReachableSum = <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/branchprobability/#afd00958cba7080048a84cccfcef55d71">BranchProbability::getZero</a>();</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00481" /><CodeLine lineNumber="481"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">for</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">auto</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/support/md5-cpp/#ac0eafdc9ee161b71e7af98af736952fd">I</a> : ReachableIdxs)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00482" /><CodeLine lineNumber="482"><span class="doxyHighlight">    OldReachableSum += BP&#91;<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/support/md5-cpp/#ac0eafdc9ee161b71e7af98af736952fd">I</a>&#93;;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00483" /><CodeLine lineNumber="483"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00484" /><CodeLine lineNumber="484"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (OldReachableSum != NewReachableSum) &#123; </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Anything to dsitribute?</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00485" /><CodeLine lineNumber="485"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (OldReachableSum.<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/branchprobability/#a6abbd0248d2ceaacdc70448659c0c2f4">isZero</a>()) &#123;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00701" /><CodeLine lineNumber="701"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// inherently has several (possibly &quot;contradicting&quot;) weights. For example,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00702" /><CodeLine lineNumber="702"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// &quot;unwind&quot; block may also contain &quot;cold&quot; call. In that case the first</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00703" /><CodeLine lineNumber="703"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// set weight is favored and all consequent weights are ignored.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00704" /><CodeLine lineNumber="704"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (!EstimatedBlockWeight.insert(&#123;BB, BBWeight&#125;).second)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00705" /><CodeLine lineNumber="705"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">false</span><span class="doxyHighlight">;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00706" /><CodeLine lineNumber="706"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00707" /><CodeLine lineNumber="707"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">for</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (BasicBlock &#42;PredBlock : <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#acb22fb04083152eee862457e42e8dc31">predecessors</a>(BB)) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00708" /><CodeLine lineNumber="708"><span class="doxyHighlight">    LoopBlock PredLoop = getLoopBlock(PredBlock);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00709" /><CodeLine lineNumber="709"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Add affected block/loop to a working list.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00710" /><CodeLine lineNumber="710"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (isLoopExitingEdge(&#123;PredLoop, LoopBB&#125;)) &#123;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00712" /><CodeLine lineNumber="712"><span class="doxyHighlight">        LoopWorkList.<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvectortemplatebase/#af42bfbc067df27c19ee2fc859df58799">push&#95;back</a>(PredLoop);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00713" /><CodeLine lineNumber="713"><span class="doxyHighlight">    &#125; </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">else</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (!EstimatedBlockWeight.count(PredBlock))</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00714" /><CodeLine lineNumber="714"><span class="doxyHighlight">      BlockWorkList.<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvectortemplatebase/#af42bfbc067df27c19ee2fc859df58799">push&#95;back</a>(PredBlock);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00715" /><CodeLine lineNumber="715"><span class="doxyHighlight">  &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00716" /><CodeLine lineNumber="716"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">true</span><span class="doxyHighlight">;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00717" /><CodeLine lineNumber="717"><span class="doxyHighlight">&#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00718" /><CodeLine lineNumber="718"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00719" /><CodeLine lineNumber="719"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Starting from \\p BB traverse through dominator blocks and assign \\p BBWeight</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00720" /><CodeLine lineNumber="720"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// to all such blocks that are post dominated by \\BB. In other words to all</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00721" /><CodeLine lineNumber="721"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// blocks that the one is executed if and only if another one is executed.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00722" /><CodeLine lineNumber="722"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Importantly, we skip loops here for two reasons. First weights of blocks in</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00723" /><CodeLine lineNumber="723"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// a loop should be scaled by trip count (yet possibly unknown). Second there is</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00724" /><CodeLine lineNumber="724"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// no any value in doing that because that doesn&#39;t give any additional</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00725" /><CodeLine lineNumber="725"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// information regarding distribution of probabilities inside the loop.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00726" /><CodeLine lineNumber="726"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Exception is loop &#39;enter&#39; and &#39;exit&#39; edges that are handled in a special way</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00727" /><CodeLine lineNumber="727"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// at calcEstimatedHeuristics.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00728" /><CodeLine lineNumber="728"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00729" /><CodeLine lineNumber="729"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// In addition, \\p WorkList is populated with basic blocks if at leas one</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00730" /><CodeLine lineNumber="730"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// successor has updated estimated weight.</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00927" /><CodeLine lineNumber="927"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// If TotalWeight is 0 that means weight of each successor is 0 as well and</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00928" /><CodeLine lineNumber="928"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// equally likely. Bail out early to not deal with devision by zero.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00929" /><CodeLine lineNumber="929"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (!FoundEstimatedWeight || TotalWeight == 0)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00930" /><CodeLine lineNumber="930"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">false</span><span class="doxyHighlight">;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00931" /><CodeLine lineNumber="931"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00932" /><CodeLine lineNumber="932"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/amdgpu/silowercontrolflow-cpp/#a4868c5d81c5ccc98c47aeab6244346a0">assert</a>(SuccWeights.<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvectortemplatecommon/#a1c479a8c434377c2b8cb056bdfdfc201">size</a>() == <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a85da2bdebeeed0bf7fdccfdfc5f1b92c">succ&#95;size</a>(BB) &amp;&amp; </span><span class="doxyHighlightStringLiteral">&quot;Missed successor?&quot;</span><span class="doxyHighlight">);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00933" /><CodeLine lineNumber="933"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> SuccCount = SuccWeights.<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvectortemplatecommon/#a1c479a8c434377c2b8cb056bdfdfc201">size</a>();</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00934" /><CodeLine lineNumber="934"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00935" /><CodeLine lineNumber="935"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// If the sum of weights does not fit in 32 bits, scale every weight down</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00936" /><CodeLine lineNumber="936"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// accordingly.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00937" /><CodeLine lineNumber="937"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (TotalWeight &gt; UINT32&#95;MAX) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00938" /><CodeLine lineNumber="938"><span class="doxyHighlight">    uint64&#95;t ScalingFactor = TotalWeight / UINT32&#95;MAX + 1;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00939" /><CodeLine lineNumber="939"><span class="doxyHighlight">    TotalWeight = 0;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00940" /><CodeLine lineNumber="940"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">for</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> Idx = 0; Idx &lt; SuccCount; ++Idx) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00941" /><CodeLine lineNumber="941"><span class="doxyHighlight">      SuccWeights&#91;Idx&#93; /= ScalingFactor;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00942" /><CodeLine lineNumber="942"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (SuccWeights&#91;Idx&#93; == </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">static&#95;cast&lt;</span><span class="doxyHighlight">uint32&#95;t</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">&gt;</span><span class="doxyHighlight">(<a href="#a0bab6cbda2c6f1e9dd352004a6b9f393a529e9e0beb5f85d1f132917c1a09860c">BlockExecWeight::ZERO</a>))</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00943" /><CodeLine lineNumber="943"><span class="doxyHighlight">        SuccWeights&#91;Idx&#93; =</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00944" /><CodeLine lineNumber="944"><span class="doxyHighlight">            </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">static&#95;cast&lt;</span><span class="doxyHighlight">uint32&#95;t</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">&gt;</span><span class="doxyHighlight">(<a href="#a0bab6cbda2c6f1e9dd352004a6b9f393a73be61fb26fc56377050ab1e85eab645">BlockExecWeight::LOWEST&#95;NON&#95;ZERO</a>);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00945" /><CodeLine lineNumber="945"><span class="doxyHighlight">      TotalWeight += SuccWeights&#91;Idx&#93;;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00946" /><CodeLine lineNumber="946"><span class="doxyHighlight">    &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00947" /><CodeLine lineNumber="947"><span class="doxyHighlight">    <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/amdgpu/silowercontrolflow-cpp/#a4868c5d81c5ccc98c47aeab6244346a0">assert</a>(TotalWeight &lt;= UINT32&#95;MAX &amp;&amp; </span><span class="doxyHighlightStringLiteral">&quot;Total weight overflows&quot;</span><span class="doxyHighlight">);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00948" /><CodeLine lineNumber="948"><span class="doxyHighlight">  &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00949" /><CodeLine lineNumber="949"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00950" /><CodeLine lineNumber="950"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Finally set probabilities to edges according to estimated block weights.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00951" /><CodeLine lineNumber="951"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a8fc529c79977cdd01e187986f960a07f">SmallVector&lt;BranchProbability, 4&gt;</a> EdgeProbabilities(</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00953" /><CodeLine lineNumber="953"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00954" /><CodeLine lineNumber="954"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">for</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> Idx = 0; Idx &lt; SuccCount; ++Idx) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00955" /><CodeLine lineNumber="955"><span class="doxyHighlight">    EdgeProbabilities&#91;Idx&#93; =</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00956" /><CodeLine lineNumber="956"><span class="doxyHighlight">        BranchProbability(SuccWeights&#91;Idx&#93;, (uint32&#95;t)TotalWeight);</span></CodeLine>
